      "name": "Desiccating Breath",
      "type": "feat",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p> The &amp;Reference[dragon]{dragon} exhales yellowish &amp;Reference[necrotic]{necrotic} energy in a 15-foot &amp;Reference[cone]{cone}. Each creature in that area must make a [[/save con 11 format=long]]. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/damage 6d6 type=necrotic average=true]] damage and is weakened until the end of its next turn. A weakened creature has disadvantage on Strength-based ability checks and &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} saving throws, and the creature’s weapon attacks that rely on &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} deal half damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage and isn’t weakened.</p>\n</section>\nThe [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]] and a save is required.\n</div>",
